- Prepared and completed the energy, AFOLU and IPPU sectors for Lebanons third BUR inventory; a south-south exchange session between Lebanon and Armenia on GHG inventories, mitigation actions and MRV arrangements; and the GHG inventory review of Lebanons second BUR to present at the Facilitative Sharing of Views at COP24;
- Coordinated with: MoEW and MoIM on the continous flow of needed information for the energy inventory, UNFCCC review team for the ICA process, E-ecosolutions and LAU on the e-motorshow in 2019, AGRICAL on the consultant recruitment, UNFCCC on the needs-based finance project, the MoET team to coordinate activities, and the DRR UNDP team on their new strategy;
- Development of new proposals: finalized the development of the NAP project proposal and GCF readiness project proposal; preparing a project proposal on GHG reducing measures for the private sector (hotels, hospitals) to submit to CTCN; prepared project document for BURIII/FNC which was approved;
- Capacity building activities: Developed data collection templates, archiving templates, QA/QC plan and uncertainly analysis for all inventory sectors under IPCC guidelines; organized 7 training sessions on GHG emissions calculation for the air quality department at MoE; drafted 3 TORs for climate change consultants as part of support provided to the AGRICAL project;
- Lebanon Climate Act (LCA): prepared a training session for Lebanon Climate Act members, prepared action plans for private companies, prepared the LCA’s third annual ceremony at IBEF 2018 and worked with NDU on setting benchmarks;
- Participated in: the IBEF 2018 event on a panel about Digitalization in Sustainable Transportation, in the LCEC-IKI regional event, the National Biodiversity Strategy and Action Plan meeting and the Global Compact Network Lebanon conferences;
- Participated in a UNFCCC training on 2006 IPCC Guidelines in Beijing, China, the GCF meeting in South Korea, and in a gender meeting in Belgrade, Serbia;
- Awareness activities: Enhanced climate awareness by presenting to individuals at Bank Audi and Bureau Veritas; Prepared and participated in an air quality and transport workshop in AUB; Participated in the UfM meeting in Barcelona, Spain; Conducted radio interview with Izeet el Nour, TV interviews with MTV and TL, and engaged stakeholders to run for climate at the Beirut marathon.
